Is it possible the group of machines are all using the same certificate 
(which lives in &#39;adhoc.keystore&#39; if you simply let it be generated when 
needed), perhaps because you copied an initial configuration everywhere?

If so, I would have expected that to work fine when accepting the 
certificate as an exception in browsers, or using the curl &#39;-k&#39; 
&quot;insecure&quot;/accept-any-certificate mode.

But, perhaps even when curl is using the &#39;-k&#39; mode, it&#39;s caching 
individual self-signed certs and refusing to use the exact same cert 
from different hosts?

Trying to connect to the same machines with a browser might yield more 
descriptive error messages. There might be a way to clear curl&#39;s cache 
between invocations to different hosts. Or, by deleting the existing 
adhoc.keystore on each machine, and relaunching the H3 application, a 
new unique local keystore should be created on each machine.

- Gordon @ IA

